<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="205" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Campbell</persName></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#left">No. 16.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-09"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 9, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch No. 15, of May 8, has been
                            received. The prompt measures adopted by you to thwart the supposed
                            schemes of rebel emissaries in Sweden, to which your attention had been
                            called <hi rend="italic">by</hi> Mr. Wood, are approved and
                            commended.</p>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * *</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">James H. Campbell,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., Stockholm.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>